  "title": "Manager, Strategic Business Development",
  "description": "<p><strong>All the responsibilities we will trust you with:</strong></p><ul><li>Drive M&A transactions including day-to-day project management</li><li>Conduct industry and market research</li><li>Work in conjunction with various professional advisors, including lawyers, to facilitate the preparation of Letters of Intent, terms sheets and Sale and Purchase Agreements</li><li>Perform hands-on rigorous financial analysis and review on target companies;</li><li>Participate in meetings among clients, counterparts and various professionals and provide support various negotiations</li><li>Provide support in new business origination</li><li>Assist in review of corporate and business unit strategy</li><li>Perform financial and valuation analyses using various methodologies</li><li>Prepare presentation materials for use in meetings with senior management</li></ul><p><strong>Your areas of knowledge and expertise that matter most for this role:</strong></p><ul><li>At least 6 to 8 years in relevant field of work </li><li>A degree in economics/accounting/business/finance with professional qualifications in accounting/ finance (such as CPA or CFA etc).</li><li>Good analytical, problem solving and presentation skills</li><li>Self-motivated and able to work under pressure</li></ul>",
